text:
Natera is the leader
in cell-free DNA analysis.
We are working in the women's health space.
We're working in oncology

and organ health, so we
had a centralized team

that was working on preparing,
exposing data to our business

and they had challenges in
regards to being able to expose
that data in time

and the innovation cycle
wasn't fast enough.

On that end. We built like
a distributed domain based
data access to the different domains
that we have within the organization.

With Amazon DataZone, we were
able to kind like, introduce
that in a way which allowed us

to really have a self-serve
approach for our teams
to be able to access that data.
We can measure things immediately.

We can look at usage, we
can look at the information

that our system systems
are generating very quickly
and with that make decisions on
what is valuable for our end users.
With AWS it's

way easier. We can leverage
those components which are
readily available and we don't really have
to focus on infrastructure,
but can focus on the business problem.
